## Context

This node defines the specification for a social login user authentication system.

## Content

- OAuth 2.0 social login (Google, GitHub)
- JWT access token + refresh token
- Refresh Token Rotation (RTR) applied on token renewal

## Rationale

OAuth 2.0 was chosen to balance security and user convenience.

## Constraints

- PII data must be stored on domestic servers only
- Access token validity: 15 minutes

## Open Questions

- Whether to add email authentication in addition to social login
